        <h2 id="email-forwarding">Email Forwarding</h2>

        <p>Getting your support emails into Helpful is the first step to providing awesome customer support.</p>

        <h3>Forward emails from a Google Apps account</h3>
        <h4>Step 1: Go to your account settings page in Google Apps</h4>
        <p>It's usually something like <a href="https://google.com/a/example.com">https://google.com/a/&lt;example.com&gt;</a>.</p>

        <h4>Step 2: Create a new group</h4>
        <p>Name it something nice (like support, or help).</p>

        <h4>Step 3: Add your forwarding address to as a member of that group</h4>
        <p>You can find your forwarding address in the settings page of your account.</p>

        <h2 id="widget">Widget</h2>

        <p>Helpful comes with Widget, a nify way to offer direct support to visitors to your website. It lets of offer awesome support right at the point when your customers need it the most.</p>

        <p>Conversations are created from the widget like they would an email, and you reply the the users via an email.</p>

        <span class="thumbnail">
          <%= image_tag 'docs/widget-preview.png' %>
        </span>

        <h3>Setup</h3>

        <p>To install Widget on your website you need to copy and paste the following code your HTML:</p>

        <pre><code>&lt;script async src="https://assets.helpful.io/widget.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>

        <p>Then add the <code>data-helpful</code> attribute to any link on your site. The value of the attribute should be the name of your account.</p>

        <pre><code>&lt;a href="#" data-helpful="&lt;HELPFUL ACCOUNT&gt;"&gt;Help!&lt;a&gt;</code></pre>

        <%= mail_to 'helpful@helpful.io', 'Widget example', data: {helpful: 'helpful'} %>

        <h3>Customize</h3>

        <p>If you already have information about your customer, you can save them typing by having it pre-filled.</p>

        <pre><code>&lt;a href="#" data-helpful="&lt;HELPFUL ACCOUNT&gt;" data-helpful-name="Jane Smith" data-helpful-email="jane@example.com"&gt;Help!&lt;a&gt;</code></pre>

        <% if signed_in? %>
          <%= mail_to 'helpful@helpful.io', 'Customized widget example', data: {helpful: 'helpful', 'helpful-email' => current_user.email, 'helpful-name' => current_user.name} %>
        <% else %>
          <%= mail_to 'helpful@helpful.io', 'Customized widget example', data: {helpful: 'helpful'} %>
        <% end %>

